---
description: Archive agent transcripts after a migration. Apply when a migration has just finished or the user asks about archiving transcripts.
applyIntelligently: true
---

After completing a migration, copy the conversation transcript(s) into the template's migration folder so they're preserved in the repo.

## Where to archive

```
templates/<name>/migrated/migration/transcripts/
  <uuid>.jsonl
  subagents/
    <sub-uuid>.jsonl
```

## How to archive

1. Find the current transcript UUID from the agent-transcripts directory.
2. Copy the main `.jsonl` file and any subagent transcripts:

```bash
TEMPLATE="<name>"
UUID="<transcript-uuid>"
SRC="$(find ~/.cursor/projects -path "*/agent-transcripts/${UUID}" -type d 2>/dev/null | head -1)"

mkdir -p "templates/${TEMPLATE}/migrated/migration/transcripts/subagents"
cp "${SRC}/${UUID}.jsonl" "templates/${TEMPLATE}/migrated/migration/transcripts/"

# Copy subagent transcripts if they exist
if [ -d "${SRC}/subagents" ]; then
  cp "${SRC}/subagents/"*.jsonl "templates/${TEMPLATE}/migrated/migration/transcripts/subagents/" 2>/dev/null
fi
```

3. If the migration spanned multiple chat sessions, repeat for each transcript UUID.
